    <h1>Naimat</h1>

    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>
        Food wastage is a growing challenge in urban areas, while at the same time many communities
        suffer from food insecurity. Restaurants, grocery stores, and households often have surplus
        food that could be redistributed if an efficient, scalable system existed.
    </p>
    <p>
        <b>Naimat</b> aims to address this gap by building a cloud-based food redistribution platform
        that connects donors with NGOs, volunteers, and individuals in need. The system leverages
        Microsoft Azure services to provide scalability, reliability, AI-powered features, and
        real-time operations.
    </p>

    <h2>Objectives</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Build a scalable cloud application to connect surplus food providers with recipients.</li>
        <li>Implement real-time matching of donors and recipients using geolocation.</li>
        <li>Enable AI-powered categorization and search to streamline food donations.</li>
        <li>Provide a transparent impact dashboard showing food saved, meals donated, and people served.</li>
        <li>Ensure secure and seamless access for donors, NGOs, recipients, and volunteers.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Core Features</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><b>Donation Posting</b> – Donors can upload food details, images, and availability.</li>
        <li><b>Pickup Coordination</b> – Matches donors with nearby NGOs/recipients and assigns volunteers.</li>
        <li><b>Location-Based Matching</b> – Uses Azure Maps for proximity-based routing.</li>
        <li><b>Food Categorization (AI-Powered)</b> – Automatically classifies food types and generates smart tags.</li>
        <li><b>Semantic Search</b> – Multilingual search using AI embeddings (English, Roman Urdu, Urdu).</li>
        <li><b>Notifications</b> – Real-time alerts for donors, volunteers, and recipients.</li>
        <li><b>Impact Dashboard</b> – Displays statistics on donations, waste reduction, and reach.</li>
        <li><b>Authentication</b> – Secure login for all user types.</li>
    </ul>

